BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (09): RUSSIA, EU, BTV-14
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 26 Nov 2012
Source: Rosselkhoznadzor, Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance [in Russian, machine trans., & summ., edited]
http://fsvps.ru/fsvps/news/5603.html


About phone calls between the Deputy Head of Rosselkhoznadzor EA Nepoklonov and the Director, Veterinary and International affairs, EC Health & Consumers (SANCO), Bernard Van Goethem
-------------------------------------------
The talks took place at the initiative of the Russian side. Eugene Nepoklonov expressed very serious concern about the spread of the bluetongue virus serotype 14 in Baltic States and Poland and Russia's needs for complete information from the EU Commission on regarding the results of monitoring of the disease.

He recalled that Rosselkhoznadzor has identified positive serological tests -- both serotypes 8 and 14 -- in animals imported from EC. Similar cases have been reported by the Belarus Veterinary Service. Bluetongue serotype 14 was, according to Rosselkhoznadzor information, detected by the Spanish veterinary service in a calf from Poland. Nepoklonov said that the Russian serological results were supported by the reference OIE laboratory at Pirbright, UK. In case the said BTV-14 is a vaccine strain, as reportedly suggested, this is concerning as well -- indicative of uncontrolled use of vaccines.

Van Goethem assured Nepoklonov that updated information on the spread of bluetongue in the EU has already been sent to the Rosselkhoznadzor, and that the European Commission is ready to carry further negotiations on this issue.

--
Communicated by:
Sabine Zentis
